cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a scientometric evaluation method for interdisciplinary units, which involves comparing papers based on their citation behavior. This could fall under several sub-categories, but the most likely ones are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these fields often deal with analyzing and processing large amounts of data, including citation data. Additionally, the paper specifically mentions the Department of Chinese Language and Linguistics, which suggests a focus on natural language processing and could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of statistical methods to assess the significance of differences among sets could also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
